description: From the creative team of Pat Mills (Charley's War) and Kevin O'Neill (The League of Extraordinary Gentlemen) comes a new kind of law enforcement for a dark and dystopian future - Marshal Law! When one of San Futuro's leading sex queen hostesses turns up dead in what appears to be a bizarre suicide, it seems clear that there is more to this insidious situation than meets the eye. It's time for Marshal Law to dish out the pain! Also featuring the classic stories "Cloak of Evil" and "Day of the Dead," this brand-new and fully-illustrated novel includes an introduction and commentary by Pat Mills, all-new digital cover art by Nick Percival, and hordes of unseen artwork by award-winning artist O'Neill!
name: TPB

description: The government has publicly endorsed genetics programs designed to create a new race of super-heroes. Now, men and women with super-powers run rampant, and a vicious and evil killer is pursuing a crazed agenda. Marshal Law stands between the city and the Abyss, and he is a hero hunter!
name: TPB

description: A hard-hitting collection of classic Marshal Law stories, including Super Babylon, Kingdom of the Blind and The Hateful Dead (originally published by Epic)! Marshal Law is back, continuing his mission to rid San Futuro - and the world - of the heroes-gone-bad who blight the city with crime. Features a new cover illustration by Kevin O'Neill and a new introduction by Pat Mills.
name: TPB

volume.name: Marshal Law: Blood, Sweat and Fears

description:
From the legendary creative team of Pat Mills and Kevin O'Neill. Marshal Law is back, continuing his mission to rid San Futuro of heroes-gone-bad who blight the city. Includes 'Marshal Law vs The Mask', featuring the maliciously madcap artefact that turns run-of-the-mill psychos into out and out homicidal maniacs!

Reprints:

  • Crime & Punishment: Marshal Law Takes Manhattan (1989) OGN
  • Marshal Law: Secret Tribunal (1993) #1- #2
  • The Mask/Marshal Law (1998) #1- #2
name: TPB

description: From the classic team of Pat Mills (Judge Dredd, ABC Warriors) and Kevin O'Neill (League of Extraordinary Gentlemen) comes this hardboiled illustrated prose thriller of "heroes" gone bad! When a pack of superhero serial killers begins to stalk the streets of San Futuro, it's time for Marshal Law to don once again the black leather and barbed wire... and dish out the pain! An all-new cover and full-color illustrations throughout by Kevin O'Neill highlight this never-before-published novella, previously available only online!
name: TPB

description: Collects all six issues of CRYSIS! Earth, 2020. United States Special Forces Major Laurence “Prophet” Barnes and the soldiers of Raptor Team thought their deployment on the Lingshan islands was a basic covert op against North Korean forces. They couldn’t have been more wrong. Archaeologists had awoken a nightmare on the island that had lain buried for millions of years–the Ceph, an alien race utterly hostile to human life. In a battle that stretches across the solar system and back, can Prophet and Raptor Team stop the aliens and save mankind?
name: TPB
